### Expected behavior

Throw the exception, don't  hide it and finish the test with Failed.

### Actual behavior

Hide exception and return without error

### Reproduction Steps

write the test case and use other azure services' SDK with the condition that SDK will throw exception

The new test framework will handle exception and close the scope immediately instead of throw the exception, which makes me be confused. For example, I call a get resource API, if the resource doesn't exist it will return 404 and some SDK will throw exception.
But test framework hide this exception and finish the call statement, and my test stuck in the running. This is not clear
This is just an example, all the exception in during call services SDKs which will be hided



### Expected behavior

Throw the exception, don't  hide it and finish the test with Failed.

### Actual behavior

Throw exception

### Reproduction Steps

write the test case and use other azure services' SDK with the condition that SDK will throw exception
